<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 6:31PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Roanoke and northwestern Franklin Counties, the City of
Salem and the City of Roanoke through 700 PM EDT...
At 631 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Poages Mill, or over Bent Mountain, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Boones Mill...
Bent Mountain...
Hollins...
and Poages Mill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
